ZH: 1. 你好，欢迎光临！请问您有什么需要吗？
EN: 1. Hello, welcome! May I help you with anything?

ZH: 2. 服务员请客人坐下，拿来菜单。
EN: 2. The waiter seated the guests and brought the menu.

ZH: 3. 客人点了一份炒面和一杯可乐。
EN: 3. The customer ordered a plate of fried noodles and a glass of cola.

ZH: 4. 今天的食物很受客人欢迎。
EN: 4. The food today is popular with the guests.

ZH: 5. 客人感到很满意，对厨师表示赞赏。
EN: 5. The guests are very satisfied and praise the chef.

ZH: 6. 客人在享用晚餐时，喜欢听轻音乐。
EN: 6. The guests enjoy listening to soft music while having dinner.

ZH: 7. 服务员礼貌地向客人介绍当天的特色菜。
EN: 7. The waiter politely introduces the guest to the special dishes of the day.

ZH: 8. 客人要求加点辣椒提味。
EN: 8. The guest requested to add some chili for extra flavor.

ZH: 9. 客人感到终于可以上桌吃饭，因为她饿了一天了。
EN: 9. The guest finally feels like getting to the table to eat, because she has been hungry all day.

ZH: 10. 服务员为客人干净地摆设餐具。
EN: 10. The waiter neatly sets the tableware for the guest.

ZH: 11. 客人看到了一个特别喜欢的菜，决定点一个。
EN: 11. The guest saw a dish that she really liked and decided to order one.

ZH: 12. 客人特别喜欢这家餐厅的烤鸡。
EN: 12. The guest really likes the roasted chicken at this restaurant.

ZH: 13. 客人想了解菜单上的每种食物的做法。
EN: 13. The guest wants to know how each dish on the menu is prepared.

ZH: 14. 服务员礼貌地问客人他们是否需要任何帮助。
EN: 14. The waiter politely asked the guest if they needed any help.

ZH: 15. 客人点了一个额外的甜点当作特别的礼物。
EN: 15. The guest ordered an extra dessert as a special treat.

ZH: 16. 服务员迎接客人时微笑着向他们引荐。
EN: 16. The waiter greeted the guests with a smile and introduced them.

ZH: 17. 客人享用餐后，表示要向经理赞美这家餐厅的服务。
EN: 17. The guest, after dining, expressed their intention to praise the service of this restaurant to the manager.

ZH: 18. 客人由于兴奋而整晚都无法入睡。
EN: 18. The guest was too excited to sleep all night.

ZH: 19. 服务员询问客人是否需要继续点菜。
EN: 19. The waiter asked the guest if they would like to order more dishes.

ZH: 20. 客人对这家餐厅的环境和食物都感到非常满意。
EN: 20. The guest is very satisfied with the environment and food of this restaurant.
